{
  "doc_id": "36425",
  "text": "In this study, a history of PSA testing was associated with a 45% excess risk of prostate cancer diagnosis. A randomised controlled study on screening effectiveness in Sweden showed that men undergoing active screening had a 2.6-fold increased risk of being diagnosed with prostate cancer during the 7-year study period . A study from Florence showed 66% increased risk of prostate cancer diagnosis in men having PSA screening over 9-year period [CITATION_1] . These results from screening tests suggest that the effect of prediagnosis PSA testing on incidence is more modest than that of formal population screening.",
